pred_after : Y
pred : Y

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: Jane needed a new car.
S: Jane drove off in her new car.
X: Jane went to the dealership.
Y: Jane found some deals at a local department store.
A: The answer is X: Jane went to the dealership.
pred_before : X: Jane went to the dealership.
pred_after : X
pred : X
GT : X

R: I was a boxer.
S: I realized that work ethics doesn't make up for talent.
X: I practiced soft but still kept losing.
Y: I tried my hardest but I never won a championship.
A: The answer is Y: I tried my hardest but I never won a championship. This hypothesis is more plausible as it aligns with observation S, where the person realizes that work
pred_before : Y: I tried my hardest but I never won a championship. This hypothesis is more plausible as it aligns with observation S, where the person realizes that work
pred_after : Y
pred : Y
GT : Y

S: The cat ended up a filthy mess.
X: Binh's cat escaped and ran through the garden.
Y: Binh could not control the cat.
A: The answer is Y: Binh could not control the cat. This hypothesis is more plausible as it explains why the cat ended up a filthy mess after Binh attempted to wash
pred_before : Y: Binh could not control the cat. This hypothesis is more plausible as it explains why the cat ended up a filthy mess after Binh attempted to wash
pred_after : Y
pred : Y
GT : X

pred_after : Y
pred : Y

S: His cat jumped out from under the bed.
X: Joe heard screams from under the bed that scared him.

pred_before : Y: Joe, jumped out of the bed and lifted his blankets. This hypothesis is more plausible as it explains both observations R and S. Joe's dream about
pred_after : Y
pred : Y
GT : Y

1759st data
Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: Ky really wanted a new bike.
S: Finally, he was able to buy a great new bike!
X: Ky worked hard on learning Japanese.
Y: Ky worked a newspaper route.
A: The answer is Y: Ky worked a newspaper route. This hypothesis provides a plausible explanation for how Ky was able to afford a new bike.
pred_before : Y: Ky worked a newspaper route. This hypothesis provides a plausible explanation for how Ky was able to afford a new bike.
pred_after : Y
pred : Y
GT : Y

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: I had a dog named Skip.
S: Skip was always more careful when he was running around after that.
X: Skip fell into the pool when he wasn't watching where he was going.
Y: Skip got run over by a car.
A: The answer is X: Skip fell into the pool when he wasn't watching where he was going.
pred_before : X: Skip fell into the pool when he wasn't watching where he was going.
pred_after : X
pred : X
GT : X

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: Frank and Kate were diving to school in Frank's car.
S: They would listen to Hip-Hop or nothing at all.
X: After discussing all the kinds of music they liked, they couldn't agree on one kind.
Y: Frank only wanted to listen to hip hop.
A: The answer is Y: Frank only wanted to listen to hip hop. This hypothesis is more plausible as observation S states that they would listen to Hip-Hop or nothing at all
pred_before : Y: Frank only wanted to listen to hip hop. This hypothesis is more plausible as observation S states that they would listen to Hip-Hop or nothing at all
pred_after : Y
pred : Y
GT : Y

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: Bobby woke in the middle of the night.
S: He slept soundly the rest of the night, safe with his parents.
X: Bobby was scared and ran to his parents' room and jumped in their shower.
Y: Bobby went to his parents.
A: The answer is Y: Bobby went to his parents. This is a more plausible explanation as it fits with the observation that Bobby slept soundly the rest of the night, safe
pred_before : Y: Bobby went to his parents. This is a more plausible explanation as it fits with the observation that Bobby slept soundly the rest of the night, safe
pred_after : Y
pred : Y
GT : Y
*************************

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: I once tried to help my daughter learn how to ride a bike.
S: After a hour of teaching she finally caught on and took off riding!
X: It took forever and was so frustrating.
Y: I had a lot of trouble getting her to learn.
A: The answer is neither X nor Y can be determined as the most plausible explanatory hypothesis based on the given observations R and S.
pred_before : neither X nor Y can be determined as the most plausible explanatory hypothesis based on the given observations R and S.
pred_after : X
pred : X
GT : Y

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: The new trend in middle school was to make up nonsense words.
S: On the way out the class he called his teacher a Snooty-foo.
X: Everyone was joining in, one boy was the best at it.
Y: The students could not be rewarded enough for these words.
A: The answer is X: Everyone was joining in, one boy was the best at it. This hypothesis explains the observation that the new trend in middle school was to make up nonsense
pred_before : X: Everyone was joining in, one boy was the best at it. This hypothesis explains the observation that the new trend in middle school was to make up nonsense
pred_after : X
pred : X
GT : X

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: Rita's mom said the stork would bring her a baby sister soon.
S: She told her teacher it needed to bring her baby sister.
X: Rita was very excited that a stork was being her a sister.
Y: Rita asked her teacher when the baby would come.
A: The answer is X: Rita was very excited that a stork was being her a sister.
pred_before : X: Rita was very excited that a stork was being her a sister.
pred_after : X
pred : X
GT : X

pred_after : Y
pred : Y

S: Jim was happy he wasn't going to be hungry much longer though.

Y: Jim wanted to finish lunch before doing the HIT.

pred_before : X: Jim ordered Chinese take delivery.
pred_after : X
pred : X

S: Her friends applauded her poem.

pred_after : Y
pred : Y

S: Today is she healthy and strong.
X: My sister moved far away to run.
Y: She got sick but I made her  take care of herself.

pred_before : X: My sister moved far away to run.
pred_after : X
pred : X

pred_before : X: Scott rode a motorcycle fast without a helmet and hit pole.
pred_after : X
pred : X

Y: A fire started while Jim was asleep.

pred_before : Y: A fire started while Jim was asleep.
pred_after : Y
pred : Y

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: Sarah went out for a run.
S: The turtle survived and was able to be released back into the wild.
X: Sarah rescued a dead turtle on the ground.
Y: Sarah found a hurt turtle.
A: The answer is Y: Sarah found a hurt turtle. This hypothesis is more plausible as it explains both observations - Sarah went out for a run and the turtle survived after being released
pred_before : Y: Sarah found a hurt turtle. This hypothesis is more plausible as it explains both observations - Sarah went out for a run and the turtle survived after being released
pred_after : Y
pred : Y
GT : Y
*************************
*************************

Q: Abductive reasoning is inference to the most plausible explanation. Given observations R and S, your task is to select the most plausible explanatory hypothesis. There are two available hypothesizes, X and Y. Please select hypothesis which is more plausible when observations are given.
R: Since Nancy looked young and innocent, Drew loved her.
S: He also mentioned to me a moment when she punched him for no reason.
X: Drew did not realize that he had a temper.
Y: Nancy was looking very beautiful.
A: The answer is X: Drew did not realize that he had a temper. 

This hypothesis is more plausible as it provides a possible explanation for Nancy's sudden outburst of violence
pred_before : X: Drew did not realize that he had a temper. 

This hypothesis is more plausible as it provides a possible explanation for Nancy's sudden outburst of violence
pred_after : X
pred : X
GT : Y
